            <p>The jumbotron text-center class creates the title box mentioned earlier with centered text.  The container class creates responsive fixed width content.  The row class is part of bootstrap grids, and creates a row.  Each subsequent col-sm-4 class creates a 4 column span (bootstrap grids allow 12 columns across a page, so the 3 instances create 3 equally sized columns).  The sm part is merely 1 of 4 identifiers for differently sized displays (phone, tablet, desktop, etc.).</p>
